  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Spontaneous intracerebral bleeding also known as spontaneous intracerebral hemorrhage (sICH)
      constitute 10-15 % of all apoplexies. The Prognosis is considerably worse than it is for the
      larger population of patients suffering from cerebral thrombosis. Development of brain edema
      seemingly contributes to the disadvantageous prognosis. However, the mechanisms behind is
      only understood fragmentarily.

      By using multimodal neuro monitoring, the investigators seek to investigate
      electrophysiological and metabolic processes, which seem to accompany the formation of edema
      and clinical deterioration in patients suffering from sICH.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
